node.text:
Josh Barnett's: Bloodsport III
Minoru Suzuki vs Chris Dickinson is coming to Bloodsport.

A big Congratulations to @pathsmith as he win the @usawrestling world team trials in Greco this weekend.
.
Pat did some of his camp with me, @bigtonynelson, @victorhenrymma and others up in Lake Arrowhead and his hard work has paid off well. Here's a little video of us drilling up there. 
.
Nice work Pat!
.
#Wrestling

node.text:
More sneak peeks from behind the upcoming videos we shot for @bjj.fanatics!
.
This is one of my favorite entries and I'm stoked showing to you guys with @bernardofariabjj. In Catch Wrestling, the toe hold is meat and potatoes stuff and chains well with tons of attacks!
.
Videos coming soon!
.
Reposted from @bernardofariabjj How To Foot Lock (Toe Hold) Your Opponent From The North South by @joshlbarnett

node.text:
I will have three new Catch Wrestling technique videos coming out soon from @bjj.fanatics. Here I get to sit down with @bernardofariabjj and show you guys some of what we filmed.
.
Enjoy!
.
Reposted from @bernardofariabjj Killer Grappling Achilles Lock by @joshlbarnett
 
#bjj #achilleslock #leglock #bjjfanatics #adcc #jiujitsu #jiujitsuforlife #oss

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by "𝕿𝖍𝖊 𝖂𝖆𝖗𝖒𝖆𝖘𝖙𝖊𝖗" Josh Barnett in Ryogoku Kokugikan. May be an image of 3 people and people standing.

node.text:
#tbt to winning the King of Pancrase title representing NJPW with my brothers Iizuka and Nakanishi in my corner. Enson Inoue was there with us too.
.
For me, I felt a lot pride to raise the flag of New Japan Pro Wrestling and for Pro Wrestling at large. Working and shooting - two sides of the same coin.
.
.
.
.
.
.

node.text:
The Warmaster will have an interview in the upcoming Infinite Worlds magazine issue 9 and to go with it, a metal AF commission was done by @solomacello!
.
Pre-order your copy as these are limited. Lupercal!
.
Reposted from @infiniteworldsmagazine Check out this bad ass portrait of former UFC Heavyweight Champion and Warhammer 40k enthusiast @joshlbarnett by @solomacello for our interview in the upcoming ninth issue of Infinite Worlds! You can pre-order IW9 or sign up for the Infinite Worlds Direct Edition Ongoing Subscription on our website now! Link in bio!

node.text:
Congrats to all the @uwfxusa and @cmmafitness athletes that went out to compete in the "King of Catch" catch wrestling tournament put on by @scientificwrestling and Luis Ojeda.
.
@victorhenrymma took 1st in both his division and the absolute and some cash for winning and submission of the tournament.
.
Johnny Robles captured 2nd in his division and the absolute because of his jerk teammate Victor.
.
Juan Soto took 1st, Mia Delgado 2nd, Jesse Meritt 1st, and David Acuna 3rd behind Vic and Johnny.
.
Congratulations to the team and especially to everyone who came out to compete. Catch Wrestling is born on the mats and in competition. Keep supporting events and building the competition structure.

node.text:
After a seminar I walked in to a small, well stocked liquor store to grab this Port Charlotte edition. No big deal as I love going whiskey hunting. I pass by a man on the way in, courtesies are exchanged and I leave to grab a quick bite.
.
Coming back to the car, the man I walked by comes up to me and goes "Hey. You trained with Karl Gotch didn't you?" Now that's a very particular thing to say and he goes on to talk about training many years ago at the Malenkos and getting to learn from Karl as well.
.
By complete random chance, I managed to run into an old worker by the name of Chris Daskas, who trained under Joe and Karl Malenko, Karl Gotch, and is a relative of George Zaharias.
.
He still does the squats and hindu pushups and swings clubs too. We talked the old times, Karl, Billy, working, and more. I always say the world is a beautiful and strange place and I had to get a photo with him. 
.
Him and his brother's shop is a wonderful spot for beer and spirits as well and I highly reccomend Hercules Liquors if you should be in Pueblo, CO.
.
Thanks for the time today Chris. The boys are always the boys.

node.text:
Here's a portrait taken by @allanamato yesterday as part of other shots taken for reference for his graphic novel: Punch - the Second Coming.
.
An Inconvenient Guide to Eternal Damnation. Part 02 of a graphic novel about the rise and return of the vanquished gods; For Punch and Punch Second Coming, Allan has used myself, Ricky Whittle, Thomas Jane, Stoya, and more as reference for the beautifully illustrated characters as drawn by artist Jonathan Marks Barravecchia.
.
Through this Kickstarter, there's lots of great art and rewards from people like Bill Sienkiewicz, David Mack, Mike Mignola, and more.
.
Head over to www.inconvenientguide.com to see more and perhaps join in.
